    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the rollback strategy is being handled by the infra team separately. what i'm really getting at is that once the middleware is gone, we're moving to stateless functions. that means there won't be a persistent agent environment anymore. the goal is to simplify the system by removing the autonomous orchestration layer entirely. do you see any technical blockers to that transition specifically?",
