      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a significant shift in architecture. Transitioning to stateless functions might indeed simplify the system, but it also eradicates intrinsic orchestration capabilities. Technical blockers could include ensuring that all necessary state transitions and inter-service communication protocols are effectively managed without the orchestration layer. We may also need to consider the implications on deployment strategies, security enforcement, and service discovery protocols. A thorough analysis of our current workflows and corresponding adjustments will be required to ensure the stateless functions can operate seamlessly in its newfound capacity. I suggest we host a dedicated meeting to strategize on fully understanding the ramifications of this change before the final approval of the amendment.",
      "source": "target",
